      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Intended function</td>
          <td colspan="3">
            Flatten expressions and ensure all unnamed expressions are 
            variable references.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Right argument</td>
          <td colspan="3">A valid <varname>Namespace</varname> AST</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Output</td>
          <td colspan="3">A valid <varname>Namespace</varname> AST</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Invariant</td>
          <td colspan="3">
            On input all expressions are nested references or calls
            involving only references.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Invariant</td>
          <td colspan="3">
            On output all function bodies consist of a string of
            expressions where each expression is either named or unnamed.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Invariant</td>
          <td colspan="3">
            On output all expressions are either calls with reference 
            arguments or references themselves.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Invariant</td>
          <td colspan="3">
            On output all unnamed expressions are references.
          </td>
        </tr>
